back to the old school.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i’m not on here much anymore. life is busy to say the least. and sometimes i just want to be in the moment rather than be looking at it through the screen on my phone. but i do miss it too. i wont lie. hopefully i’ll find a balance and be back more regularly one day. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
but for now i’m going to take one thing back to the old school— ig used to be about “your life in photos”. simple, organic, real. but now it’s stories, and reels, and aesthetic, and too much thinking before posting. i’m gonna go back to posting a random photo because it makes me happy and for absolutely no reason at all.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
anyone else miss that “no pressure” posting? i do. so here’s one just because. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the old ig 
the good life
a pretty picture
a funny moment
happiness captured
there is beauty in simplicity

little people, big dreams. ⁣
my little crew is enjoying this lull between christmas and the new year. the decorations have been taken down and packed away for next year. the purging of things, decluttering and organizing is on fire. and the quality time is the best part. we’re getting ready for a new year full of new opportunities. 

i don’t really believe in making new year’s resolutions. instead i use this as a time to plan my intentions & goals for the next year. it’s nice to have something to work towards. you can always do better, right? 

what are your 2024 plans?

the kids are back to their regular school schedule and i’m back to work. it’s a bitter sweet return because we had a great break— some much needed quality time, major purging of the house, little girls are sharing a room and big girl got her own.. big changes, refreshing changes, for a new year.. 

how was your winter break? ready to take on a new year?

blah. blah. blah. ⁣

deciding to keep unnecessary negativity out of 2024 has been game changing. i’m no longer participating in cynical conversations that don’t serve anyone. instead i’ve consciously decided to change the narrative to one focusing on the positive aspects of a situation. being grateful for what my life is rather than focusing on what it could be.

this includes trying to do the same for family & friends— helping shift any interaction in a healthier direction. 

highly recommend. 

having said that— what is something you are grateful for that you don’t acknowledge enough? — whatever it is deserves your attention more than what’s bothering you right now… trust me… 🤍
